Events :
Every action which can change the state of an object is known as an event.

button(object) -------> click(action) --------> state change
                            |
                          Event                                
                            |-- Event Handler
                            |-- Event Handler Function

Example : <button onclick="alert('Button Clicked')">
          Here onclick is Event Handler
          and alert('Button Clicked') is Event Handler function 

Types of Event : 
    a. Mouse Event
        |-- onmouseover
        |-- onmousemove
        |-- onmouseup
        |-- onmousedown
        |-- onmousewheel
        |-- onmouseenter
        |-- onmouseleave
        |-- click event
                |-- onclick
                |-- obdblclick (dbl means double)
                |-- oncontextmenu (for right click)
    b. Key Event
        |-- onkeyup
        |-- onkeydown
        |-- onkeypress
    c. Form Event
        |-- onsubmit
        |-- onchange
        |-- onfocus (input events)
        |-- onblur (input events)
    d. Load Event
        |-- onload
        |-- onunload
    etc

In case of HTML : 
Elements
    |-- div,button
    |-- img
    |-- input etc
Attributes
    |-- style
    |-- src, height, width
    |-- type, name, value etc

In case of JavaScript : 
object<----->Elements
    |-- div,button
    |-- img
    |-- input etc
properties<------->Attributes
    |-- style
    |-- src, height, width
    |-- type, name, value etc